Unmounted material. Dorsal surface metallic and mirror-like (J.H. Martin, notes). “Differs from type [
Lecanium expansum
] in having a beautiful metallic sheen on dorsum of living insect, disappearing after treatment with potash.” Green, 1904, p. 205).

